The paper discusses the extraction of deep features for computer vision tasks, which is a common topic in the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also compares the performance of features extracted from a softmax-based network and those from a distance metric learning (DML) based network, which falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the size of the dataset, which is relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-categories.
